    Neoantigen T-Cell Receptor Gene Therapy in Pancreatic Cancer.
The engineered T cells constituted more than 2% of al the circulating peripheral-blood T cells 6 months after the cell transfer. In this patient, TCR gene therapy targeting the KRAS G12D driver mutation mediated the objective regression of metastatic pancreatic cancer. (Funded by the Providence Portland Medical Foundation.).
